The paper deals with change detection in aerial images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed task of semantic change pattern analysis involves analyzing both where and what changes happen, which requires semantic understanding of the images. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the task involves analyzing high-level information and making use of semantic information, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of metrics and experiments, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with aerial images, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
